text.section:
A person who acts in good faith is not civilly liable for:
Making a report under § 19-347 of the Health - General Article;
Participating in an investigation arising out of a report under § 19-347 of the Health - General Article;
Participating in a judicial proceeding arising out of a report under § 19-347 of the Health - General Article; or
Participating in transferring, suspending, or terminating the employment of any individual who is believed to have abused or aided in abusing a resident under § 19-347 of the Health - General Article.
